{
  "texts": [
    "They have explained the Kannada NER which is used to recognize the several words written in the Kannada text document using rule-based approach (RBA) [57] with good accuracy of 89.32%.",
    "Sugiarta and Sanjaya [60] proposed a method for detecting the location marking entities of Balinese text documents using Rule based approach of NER which is very challenging task.",
    "They have used recall, precision and F-measure for evaluation which is having 0.93, 0.93 and 0.92 accuracy for location entities and they have proved that this system is also able to recognize NER written Balinese text documents.",
    "Neuberger et al. [61] demonstrated an addition to the dataset using information extraction phase (PET) that includes the details on linguistic suggestions and mechanism for resolving them and also presented a comprehensive analysis of the key problems with the dataset.",
    "Riaz [62] has discussed about the issue of Named Entity Recognition, particularly the problem of its languages without having the sufficient linguistic resources such as large annotated corpora and also focused the challenges of NER for Urdu language which differentiate from other South Asian languages."
  ]
}